Title: Object: The Tenth Plague of Egypt
Series: Liber Studiorum
Description: Buildings and towers on the right and a temple high up on the far left with trees below; in the foreground women in various postures, one stooping over a dead child; lightning overhead. 1 January 1816 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Joseph Mallord William Turner
Bibliographic references: Finberg 1924 / The History of Turner's Liber Studiorum with a new catalogue raisonné (61) (etching)
Acquisition notes: See 1852,1009.1141 for a note on the donation of Say’s prints.
